00:19.890 --> 00:22.460
- Can you hear me, Mr. Morden?
- Yes.

00:22.493 --> 00:26.431
<i>Cue the recap!
Paraguay vacay made me this way.</i>

00:26.463 --> 00:29.600
<i>A harbinger of chaos brought
to make this geezer pay.</i>

00:29.634 --> 00:33.005
I strung along the Dumb Patrol,
<i>flipped the bus into a hole,</i>

00:33.037 --> 00:36.607
<i>slammed it shut. Wait, what?
Stuffed it up a donkey's butt!</i>

00:36.609 --> 00:38.475
- Any sign of the Chief?
- We know he's alive.

00:38.475 --> 00:40.478
<i>A team was
forged with one belief,</i>

00:40.512 --> 00:44.247
<i>to stop at nothing
and get their Chief.</i>

00:44.281 --> 00:46.417
<i>Nazi-beating,
doomsday-cheating,</i>

00:46.451 --> 00:48.552
<i>beard hair-eating,
romance-hating,</i>

00:48.585 --> 00:50.354
<i>punk to skunk, robot chunk,</i>

00:50.387 --> 00:52.222
flashback dancing with a hunk,

00:52.256 --> 00:54.424
<i>gator-baiting,
half chub-dating,</i>

00:54.459 --> 00:56.426
<i>sliming through
a metal grating,</i>

00:56.460 --> 00:59.597
<i>death cult all around,
Jane survived the Underground,</i>

00:59.631 --> 01:03.267
<i>Ant Farm, Larry harmed,
delivering justice with a swarm.</i>

01:03.301 --> 01:04.736
- No!
<i>- Father-doting,</i>

01:04.769 --> 01:08.338
<i>hand-exploding, pain obscured
through secret coding.</i>

01:08.373 --> 01:10.240
<i>Growing close
with each endeavor,</i>

01:10.274 --> 01:11.977
<i>finally they came together.</i>

01:12.010 --> 01:14.379
<i>But I grew bored</i>

01:14.412 --> 01:15.513
<i>with this game of chase</i>

01:15.546 --> 01:17.649
<i>and trapped them inside
the white space.</i>

01:17.682 --> 01:19.316
<i>Backed their leader
against the wall,</i>

01:19.349 --> 01:21.084
<i>forcing him to spill it all.</i>

01:21.117 --> 01:23.953
I was responsible
for everything

01:23.987 --> 01:25.924
that has happened
to each of you.

01:25.956 --> 01:30.367
<i>This is
the best timeline ever!</i>

02:48.171 --> 02:49.372
Why?

02:49.407 --> 02:52.175
I needed you.

02:52.209 --> 02:54.344
I wanted...

02:54.377 --> 02:57.314
what you have.

02:57.348 --> 02:58.748
Immortality.

02:58.782 --> 03:00.683
What?

03:00.717 --> 03:04.187
I wanted to...

03:04.221 --> 03:07.358
I needed to...

03:07.390 --> 03:11.094
Motherfucker!

03:13.030 --> 03:14.798
I'm so sorry.

03:20.804 --> 03:23.106
Liar.

03:23.139 --> 03:24.974
You lied to Jane.

03:25.008 --> 03:28.012
You lied to all of us.

03:38.423 --> 03:41.272
Please let them go.

03:44.429 --> 03:46.663
What do you take me for, Niles?

03:46.698 --> 03:49.633
This was never about them.

03:49.667 --> 03:52.036
Making Silly Putty
out of their fragile,

03:52.068 --> 03:54.138
fractured brains,

03:54.170 --> 03:55.973
well, that...

03:56.006 --> 03:58.109
that was all just

03:58.141 --> 04:00.692
extra-curricular.

04:03.514 --> 04:05.550
Consider them
abandoned conquests.

04:05.582 --> 04:07.953
Their future is their own now.

04:07.985 --> 04:09.888
God, I wonder what
they'll do with it. Hmm?

04:09.920 --> 04:11.956
What does a family do
when they realize

04:11.990 --> 04:14.592
they're no family at all?
They're just rats

04:14.626 --> 04:16.394
in neighboring cages.

04:16.427 --> 04:19.163
They're just petri dishes
on the same shelf.

04:19.196 --> 04:21.966
You know,
I huffed and I puffed,

04:22.000 --> 04:24.867
but it was you all along,
wasn't it, Niles?

04:24.867 --> 04:28.839
You destroyed them!

04:28.872 --> 04:33.872
Just like you destroyed
Eric Morden.

04:34.579 --> 04:38.182
So you've had your revenge.

04:38.214 --> 04:39.651
What now?

04:39.684 --> 04:43.254
Why,
sky's the limit, old friend.

04:43.288 --> 04:46.189
I'm going to conduct a parade,
I'm gonna guest-host <i>The View,</i>

04:46.223 --> 04:47.891
I'm gonna become
the next Bachelor!

04:47.925 --> 04:50.427
The world is a golden oyster
for me now.

04:50.428 --> 04:52.295
But for you,

04:52.329 --> 04:54.932
Niles Caulder,

04:54.966 --> 04:59.966
I envision a story
that's a little different.

05:00.550 --> 05:05.571
I've been waiting decades
to ask you this.

05:06.571 --> 05:11.411
How does it feel
to be a nobody?

05:31.935 --> 05:33.971
<i>Security to
Containment Block Seven.</i>

05:34.004 --> 05:38.776
<i>All security to
Containment Block Seven.</i>

05:38.810 --> 05:41.245
- Good morning, Joshua.
- Bureau astronomers have

05:41.245 --> 05:42.547
confirmed your calculations.

05:42.579 --> 05:45.483
Next week's X-15 test flight
is our clearest shot yet

05:45.516 --> 05:47.451
to intercept the space anomaly.

05:47.485 --> 05:49.653
- Very good then.
- Meaning, after we knock

05:49.687 --> 05:50.988
this pilot from the sky...

05:51.021 --> 05:52.622
His name is
Larry Trainor by the way,

05:52.656 --> 05:54.925
Captain Larry Trainor,
wife, two kids.

05:54.959 --> 05:56.995
After we expose him
to unknown space matter,

05:57.028 --> 05:58.997
after we potentially burn
and radiate him

05:59.029 --> 06:01.833
beyond the known limits
of human capacity,

06:01.865 --> 06:03.668
then we're gonna
hand him over to Forsythe

06:03.701 --> 06:05.502
and his animals? For what?

06:05.536 --> 06:07.637
And Forsythe will
grow bored with his new toy,

06:07.672 --> 06:09.807
and then he'll be ours.
Hopefully forever.

06:09.841 --> 06:11.209
The Immortus Project
is working.

06:11.242 --> 06:15.045
Rita Farr has shown
zero signs of aging since 1955.

06:15.079 --> 06:18.281
We already have
a perfectly good test subject.

06:18.314 --> 06:21.165
Now we'll have two.

06:24.721 --> 06:29.593
Where's the line, Niles?

06:29.627 --> 06:31.629
'Cause I can't see it anymore.

06:31.661 --> 06:34.732
The only thing that should
trouble you, Joshua,

06:34.766 --> 06:36.067
is the alternative.

06:36.100 --> 06:39.937
Except I don't know
what the alternative is.

06:39.971 --> 06:44.341
The only way I sleep
at night is because...

06:44.375 --> 06:48.278
you tell me nothing.

06:48.312 --> 06:53.211
You're right.
And you're welcome.

07:05.196 --> 07:08.045
Oh, God.

07:14.139 --> 07:16.607
- Good morning, Larry.
- Apparently it is.

07:19.911 --> 07:23.180
I've been looking forward
to this day all semester.

07:23.214 --> 07:27.084
My students are finally
performing their scene studies,

07:27.117 --> 07:29.519
and I can't wait
to see how they utilize

07:29.553 --> 07:31.288
the techniques
that I've taught them.

07:31.322 --> 07:36.226
I suspect I'll be
handing out a lot of A's.

07:36.259 --> 07:37.528
Uh-huh.

07:37.562 --> 07:40.331
It feels so good to give back
to the community.

07:40.363 --> 07:42.098
We should've
done this ages ago.

07:42.100 --> 07:44.168
- What?
- Move on.

07:44.201 --> 07:46.637
Six months ago we learned
our lives had been destroyed

07:46.637 --> 07:48.773
by a madman.
Excuse me if it takes

07:48.773 --> 07:53.773
more than a moment
to get back my sea legs.

07:56.781 --> 07:58.415
When we moved into this place,

07:58.449 --> 07:59.918
we made a promise
to each other.

07:59.951 --> 08:04.120
- I know, but...
- No more hiding.

08:04.120 --> 08:05.122
I know.

08:05.154 --> 08:07.855
- I'm trying.
- Mmm.

08:44.027 --> 08:45.976
Okay.

08:50.333 --> 08:51.635
What do you think?

08:51.668 --> 08:54.504
You wanna try
for 20 seconds this time?

08:57.206 --> 08:59.342
Negative Spirit, release!

09:04.649 --> 09:08.249
Huh.

09:13.825 --> 09:16.527
There you go, buddy.

09:16.559 --> 09:18.562
We can do this.

09:18.596 --> 09:22.346
We can do this.
We can...

09:27.505 --> 09:31.341
Hit the bricks, sister.
We're... we're done. Finito.

09:31.341 --> 09:32.341
You don't mean that, Kyle.

09:32.341 --> 09:34.379
I know you better
than you know yourself.

09:34.412 --> 09:37.881
You wanna pick me up
in those strong arms.

09:37.914 --> 09:41.351
Cut. Cut.

09:41.384 --> 09:43.153
Jagger, Esme,

09:43.187 --> 09:46.890
you failed
to move your audience.

09:46.923 --> 09:50.760
We didn't feel it
because you didn't feel it.

09:50.794 --> 09:53.663
Mmm? Let me show
what it looks like

09:53.697 --> 09:58.697
when you really connect
to your character.

10:02.105 --> 10:06.905
And... action!

10:06.977 --> 10:09.312
Hit the bricks, sister.

10:09.346 --> 10:11.381
We're done. Finito.

10:11.414 --> 10:15.186
You don't mean that, Kyle. Hmm?

10:15.220 --> 10:18.655
I know you
better than you know yourself.

10:18.688 --> 10:22.559
You wanna pick me up
in these strong arms

10:22.592 --> 10:27.163
and devour me whole.

10:27.197 --> 10:28.697
And scene.

10:32.636 --> 10:35.173
And that, children,

10:35.206 --> 10:38.676
Is what serious dedication
to your craft gets you.

10:38.708 --> 10:40.677
Being a shitty high school
drama teacher?

10:40.711 --> 10:43.714
Wow. Dare to dream.

10:43.748 --> 10:45.182
It's scary not to excel

10:45.182 --> 10:47.717
at something we aspire
to do, isn't it, Esme?

10:47.751 --> 10:49.519
I'm not excelling?

10:49.552 --> 10:51.422
I can't think
of anything sadder

10:51.455 --> 10:52.923
than some washed-up never-was

10:52.956 --> 10:55.759
who gets their jollies off
out-acting a bunch of teenagers

10:55.793 --> 10:57.894
who only took this class
for the easy A.

11:10.072 --> 11:11.609
Larry!

11:11.642 --> 11:14.379
Hurry up! You're missing
the booty song.

11:14.412 --> 11:17.981
Do either of you two
want to buy Marvin Gardens?

11:18.015 --> 11:19.317
Honestly,
I could use the cash.

11:19.350 --> 11:22.687
Hmm. Larry! This is
absolutely unacceptable!

11:22.720 --> 11:24.389
1976 is ending,

11:24.422 --> 11:29.422
and you're stalling
like some truculent schoolboy.

11:38.001 --> 11:43.001
Uh, now, I believe
it's your turn.

11:44.075 --> 11:48.078
Ugh, I look ridiculous.

11:48.111 --> 11:51.181
No.

11:51.215 --> 11:53.317
Now, then, Rita,

11:53.350 --> 11:54.684
that's not fair.

11:59.057 --> 12:02.994
Oh, yeah, sure. Laugh it up.

12:03.027 --> 12:05.897
All right. Keep playing.

12:05.929 --> 12:07.432
And don't cheat.

12:07.465 --> 12:09.465
- He's talking to you.
- Uh-huh.

12:19.910 --> 12:21.778
Forsythe.

12:21.812 --> 12:23.780
What the hell
are you doing here?

12:23.813 --> 12:25.816
Wonderful home, Dr. Caulder.

12:25.850 --> 12:27.650
And a happy New Year's Eve.

12:27.684 --> 12:29.452
You need to leave.

12:29.485 --> 12:31.322
Oh.

12:31.355 --> 12:34.825
I'm afraid the matter at hand
is rather urgent.

12:34.859 --> 12:37.260
What is it?

12:37.293 --> 12:38.730
You know,

12:38.764 --> 12:42.499
when the brass told me in '68
I'd be losing Captain Trainor

12:42.533 --> 12:44.835
to your Immortus Initiative,

12:44.869 --> 12:47.004
I have to say,
I couldn't have imagined

12:47.038 --> 12:50.206
his new assignment would
be quite so...

12:50.240 --> 12:51.241
cozy.

12:51.275 --> 12:54.044
Mmm. Well, you have
your methods, I have mine.

12:54.077 --> 12:57.147
The work we do here
is just as essential.

12:57.179 --> 12:58.482
Yes.

12:58.515 --> 13:01.052
I can see that now.

13:01.085 --> 13:02.620
What is that song?

13:02.653 --> 13:04.687
My daughter likes that one.

13:04.721 --> 13:08.322
Cut the bullshit, Agent.

13:09.759 --> 13:11.962
What's that?

13:11.995 --> 13:14.498
Well, I believe
you once called it

13:14.530 --> 13:16.100
the "unrelenting",

13:16.134 --> 13:20.104
uncompromising pursuit
of truth."

13:20.138 --> 13:22.105
Your signature is
required, Doctor.

13:22.139 --> 13:23.975
Our investigators
have identified

13:24.008 --> 13:26.977
your next test subject.

13:27.010 --> 13:32.010
What are you talking about?
I... I never...

13:36.287 --> 13:39.090
That request was made
over a decade ago.

13:39.123 --> 13:40.424
And now we've found her.

13:40.457 --> 13:43.960
Hispanic female,
multiple personality disorder.

13:43.961 --> 13:48.499
By all accounts,
a real wildcat.

13:48.499 --> 13:49.668
I think you'll agree

13:49.701 --> 13:54.701
she fits perfectly the profile
you asked us to find.

14:24.534 --> 14:26.070
Jane.

14:26.104 --> 14:29.573
- Did you know?
- About what?

14:29.607 --> 14:34.607
About what that sadistic fuck
did to us, you fucking...

14:36.746 --> 14:40.717
No, no, no.

14:40.750 --> 14:44.687
He promised!

14:44.721 --> 14:48.392
Jane.

14:48.424 --> 14:53.163
Jane.

14:53.197 --> 14:57.568
Hey, it's okay.

14:57.601 --> 15:00.171
He was going to cage us here.

15:00.203 --> 15:02.673
Cage us like the rest of them.

15:02.706 --> 15:04.174
Wasn't he?

15:04.207 --> 15:06.477
Singing caged birdies

15:06.510 --> 15:11.510
with pretty feathers
for the master to pluck!

15:12.317 --> 15:16.886
It's okay.

15:16.921 --> 15:18.421
It's okay.

15:22.592 --> 15:27.431
Just tell me. Please.

15:27.464 --> 15:30.067
I knew.

15:30.100 --> 15:32.370
I can give you
the spiel, but...

15:32.403 --> 15:35.139
the truth is, I was blind.

15:35.173 --> 15:38.975
Willfully blind.

15:39.009 --> 15:42.212
You need to make it go away.

15:42.245 --> 15:45.883
- I know it's difficult...
- You don't know.

15:45.916 --> 15:49.787
I keep having this dream.

15:49.820 --> 15:53.990
I find a wound on my chest.

15:54.024 --> 15:58.363
This old wound
that's scabbed over.

15:58.395 --> 16:01.731
And I know
I shouldn't touch it,

16:01.764 --> 16:04.335
but I keep reaching for it,

16:04.369 --> 16:06.538
and I can't help but scratch.

16:06.571 --> 16:10.274
And the wound gets bigger
and bigger

16:10.307 --> 16:15.258
until there's
nothing of me left.

16:19.049 --> 16:21.485
There's a drug.

16:21.518 --> 16:24.288
An opiate.

16:24.322 --> 16:26.756
For meta-human powers.

16:26.789 --> 16:29.059
Niles created it.

16:29.092 --> 16:32.897
Gave it to me
for safe keeping,

16:32.929 --> 16:34.899
so he wouldn't be tempted.

16:44.075 --> 16:46.845
It's not a fix or a cure.

16:46.878 --> 16:49.046
It calms the noise,
it makes it more manageable,

16:49.080 --> 16:52.917
but it doesn't discriminate.

16:52.950 --> 16:55.852
Jane, it quiets everything.

16:55.885 --> 16:59.289
The good and the bad.

16:59.323 --> 17:02.159
In order to use it safely,

17:02.192 --> 17:04.194
we'd have to stick
to a strict regimen.

17:04.228 --> 17:09.228
I have to monitor
your dosage, vitals...

18:19.135 --> 18:21.071
I'm sorry, Kay.

18:21.105 --> 18:23.106
It's okay.

18:23.140 --> 18:26.140
It feels better now.

18:51.167 --> 18:53.069
- Niles?
- Huh?

18:53.104 --> 18:55.653
Elinore? Elinore.

18:58.241 --> 19:03.114
Thank you for coming.

19:03.146 --> 19:05.450
This...

19:05.482 --> 19:08.385
He's my last research subject.

19:08.419 --> 19:12.655
He was a race car driver.

19:12.689 --> 19:15.058
Father.

19:15.092 --> 19:19.262
Husband.

19:19.297 --> 19:22.596
I'm afraid all that...

19:24.568 --> 19:29.568
This is hitting me
the hardest of all.

19:30.607 --> 19:34.944
The crash was supposed
to be on the racetrack.

19:34.979 --> 19:37.582
No one else was to get hurt.

19:37.615 --> 19:41.085
No one what?
What does that mean, he was "supposed to"?

19:41.117 --> 19:43.621
How would you know...

19:43.654 --> 19:45.388
that a man is
supposed to crash?

19:45.423 --> 19:48.492
It's all gone too far.

19:48.526 --> 19:50.259
It's all gone too far, Elinore.

19:50.260 --> 19:52.229
I used to think
I had no alternative.

19:52.262 --> 19:56.032
That there wasn't
an alternative, but it's...

19:56.067 --> 20:00.837
gone too far.

20:00.871 --> 20:02.070
Niles...

20:07.877 --> 20:10.582
I love you...

20:10.615 --> 20:14.117
as a mentor and a friend.

20:14.151 --> 20:15.353
And you are scaring

20:15.385 --> 20:18.221
the ever-loving fuck
out of me right now.

20:18.256 --> 20:22.859
I need to tell you something.

20:22.893 --> 20:26.196
And I need you to promise

20:26.230 --> 20:30.334
when it's finished

20:30.367 --> 20:35.018
that you'll still be my friend.

20:39.210 --> 20:41.912
Cliff! Your order's up.

20:41.912 --> 20:42.912
Yo!

21:56.921 --> 22:00.223
You know how much
I cared for Elinore.

22:00.257 --> 22:03.294
She would have
wanted it this way.

22:03.326 --> 22:06.596
For Victor to survive.

22:06.631 --> 22:10.667
There's some comfort in that.

22:10.701 --> 22:13.336
Cold comfort.

22:13.371 --> 22:14.971
But thank you.

22:15.005 --> 22:16.641
If I may...

22:16.673 --> 22:19.509
one piece of advice.

22:19.544 --> 22:21.645
If there's one thing
I've learned from my research,

22:21.679 --> 22:24.382
Victor is going
to need special care.

22:24.414 --> 22:26.584
No offense,

22:26.616 --> 22:28.720
but we are not talking

22:28.752 --> 22:32.490
about homeschooling
my son's recovery here.

22:32.522 --> 22:33.857
S.T.A.R. Labs has it covered.

22:33.892 --> 22:37.929
I'm not talking
about technology or facilities.

22:37.961 --> 22:42.333
There's a holistic component
to be considered.

22:42.365 --> 22:45.670
Patience. Empathy.

22:45.702 --> 22:47.605
And I'm not capable
of giving it.

22:47.637 --> 22:49.306
Is that what you're saying?

22:49.339 --> 22:53.539
No, I'm... I just suggest...

22:55.011 --> 22:56.814
You might be surprised

22:56.847 --> 23:01.847
just how much of a tonic
compassion can be.

23:03.054 --> 23:05.722
And exactly who do you think
you're fooling here?

23:05.722 --> 23:10.528
Hmm? You talk
about compassion? Empathy?

23:10.560 --> 23:12.778
Like you invented it?

23:13.663 --> 23:17.087
I'm...

23:17.087 --> 23:20.570
I was her husband.

23:20.571 --> 23:24.075
And you don't think
she told me what you did?

23:24.108 --> 23:29.717
You think you have any standing
to lecture me about family?

23:30.500 --> 23:33.416
I just put
my son back together.

23:33.451 --> 23:35.019
My son!

23:35.053 --> 23:37.788
And you think that
you and I are the same?

23:37.821 --> 23:41.358
You think what you did...

23:41.392 --> 23:44.394
and what I did are the same?

23:44.428 --> 23:47.096
This wasn't some experiment.

23:47.096 --> 23:49.333
I turned my...

23:49.366 --> 23:53.671
sweet, affable, athletic,

23:53.704 --> 23:57.541
charming, delicious boy

23:57.541 --> 24:01.077
into a freak of nature.

24:01.111 --> 24:04.749
I did it out of love.

24:04.781 --> 24:07.351
Why the hell
did you do it, Niles?

24:07.384 --> 24:09.353
To those people?

24:09.386 --> 24:14.057
You speak to me
about compassion?

24:14.090 --> 24:16.626
Don't ever.

24:16.661 --> 24:18.911
Don't you dare.

24:40.483 --> 24:42.185
Who are you?

24:42.219 --> 24:43.788
Me?

24:43.820 --> 24:47.990
I'm you.

24:59.604 --> 25:01.439
Hey, Dad.

25:01.471 --> 25:04.141
<i>You okay, son?</i>

25:04.173 --> 25:06.044
Fine. Um...

25:06.076 --> 25:08.179
Just been up all night
working that bitcoin ring.

